# GitHub CODEOWNERS — auto-assigns reviews for security-critical paths.
#
# Syntax: <pattern>  <@owner1> <@owner2> ...
# First matching pattern wins (so place more-specific patterns later).
#
# Anyone in the "owner" team automatically receives a review request when
# a PR touches a matching file. Combined with branch protection's
# "require review from CODEOWNERS", this enforces that nobody (not even
# the BDFL via squash-merge) can land a change to these paths without
# explicit owner approval.

# ── Catch-all — bdfl is the fallback reviewer ───────────────────────
